SUMMARY:The High Sonomen at Redwood Cafe
DESCRIPTION:Four veterans of the Sonoma County music scene — Dave Hooper\, Paul Riley\, Dave Hamilton\, and Ken Risling — walk the high-wire without a net! That’s right\, they will be performing their own songs only. Some brand new\, but many award winners that have delighted audiences for years. All together on the Hopmonk stage for the first time in history!\nDave Hooper — For decades\, known in Nashville\, Austin\, and Europe as the front man of “Dave Hooper and the Corporate Monkeys”\, currently performs with Hooper and Sloss.\nPaul Riley — Familiar host of many variety music shows\, he fronted both The Feud and St. Peterbilt.\nDave Hamilton — Voted “Best” numerous times in numerous local music competitions\, including the Bohemian’s annual reader polls\, because\, well\, he is.\nKen Risling — Songs and/or recordings have won statewide competitions and national airplay. Former host of West Coast Songwriters competition. Now a proud member of The AOKs
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/the-high-sonomen-at-redwood-cafe/
LOCATION:Redwood Cafe\, 8240 Old Redwood Hwy\, Cotati\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
