SUMMARY:Ben Roy at The Mystic Theatre
DESCRIPTION:Get ready to laugh out loud with a night of stand-up comedy in McNear’s upstairs Red Bull Room! Food and drink specials available\, making it the perfect night out in historic downtown Petaluma! Grab your crew\, grab a drink\, and get ready for a hilarious night you won’t forget! Seating is limited—don’t wait! 7PM Doors – Show: 8PM \nCOMEDY CENTRAL \nHBO \nHULU \nVARIETY’S TOP TEN COMICS TO WATCH \nIf you aren’t familiar with Ben Roy\, he’s been taking comedy audiences by storm since 2004\, bringing an unparalleled energy and unique voice to the stage. Often compared to Lewis Black or Bill Hicks due to his passionate\, ranting approach\, Roy has a style that is definitively his own. \nRoy cut his comedic teeth in Denver at the world famous Comedy Works. Since then\, Ben has been selected to perform at the Montreal Just for Laughs Comedy Festival (for New Faces\, The Nasty Show\, and his own hour show)\, Just For Laughs Toronto\, Just For Laughs Chicago\, The New York Comedy Festival\, Austin’s South by Southwest festival (where he was an official invitee for both music and comedy in the same year)\, and many more. \nRoy has been featured on HBO’s Funny as Hell series; as well as on the Comedy Central shows Adam DeVine’s House Party\, Corporate\, @midnight\, This Is Not Happening\, and TruTV’s Talk Show The Game Show. Ben has also released five stand-up comedy albums and was listed as one of Variety’s Top 10 Comics to Watch. In 2023 his first streaming stand up special\, ‘HYENA’\, was released on YouTube by 800LB Gorilla Media. That same year NPR listed ‘HYENA’ as one of their Top Specials Of 2023. From that success\, ‘HYENA’ was licensed by HULU and Disney+ and began streaming on their platforms in July of 2024. Ben will be recording his sixth album at the world famous Comedy Works Downtown in January 2026. \nAlong with fellow Denver Comedians Adam Cayton-Holland and Andrew Orvedahl (who collectively perform as The Grawlix)\, Ben also created\, wrote\, and starred in the original comedy series Those Who Can’t that ran for three seasons on TruTV and HBOMax. \nHe’s also currently the host of two podcasts\, 97.9 The Rat Race and Advice Fight. \nIn addition to stand-up comedy\, acting\, podcasting\, and writing\, Roy is a prolific musician and the current lead singer of pop punk outfit SPELLS\, signed to indie label Snappy Little Numbers Records\, and hardcore/metal band Arson Charge\, currently signed to Anxious & Angry Records.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/ben-roy-at-the-mystic-theatre/
LOCATION:Mystic Theatre & Music Hall\, 23 Petaluma Blvd N\, Petaluma\, CA
CATEGORIES:Comedy
GEO:38.2334;-122.64
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Mystic Theatre & Music Hall 23 Petaluma Blvd N Petaluma CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=23 Petaluma Blvd N:geo:-122.64,38.2334
END:VEVENT
